replies.msg:
Welsh midfielder Aaron Ramsey rejected moves to a host of clubs including Real Madrid and Barcelona before agreeing to a Juventus move in the summer according to BBC journalist David Ornstein.<br />
<br />
He claimed: &quot;Real Madrid, Inter Milan, Paris-Saint Germain a very good offer from them as well, Bayern Munich and some preliminary talks with Barcelona as well, so Ramsey had the upper hand in these negotiations...It seems Juventus, who were always his preferred choice from a footballing perspective, seem to come up trumps on the money side as well.&quot;

